reviews.headline: My FAVORITE eyeshadow hands-down
reviews.comments: I had been off eyeshadow [and most makeup] for years before stumbling upon this. The glitter makes my millenial heart sing - it doesn't irritate my sensitive eyes and stays on all day long. Can be subtle or full-on depending on how much you layer it. Into it/over it is *chefs kiss*

reviews.headline: Obsessed
reviews.comments: I am absolutely OBSESSED with this product every time I wear it I get SO many compliments on my eyes!

reviews.headline: Love this!
reviews.comments:
This is my favorite brand of cream eyeshadow sticks!  My other favorite is Ulta cream eye shadow stick! 
It's creamy, it blends well and it stays on! I get compliments about how sparkly it is even without the glitter side of the pencil! sometimes I put the glitter at the inside corner of my eyes too!

reviews.headline: I tell everyone about this product!
reviews.comments: I don't really write reviews but this product has to be one of my favorite products that I've bought from ulta. I had used this eyeshadow combo for a concert and got a few compliments. It is so easy to use and you can always take it on the go.

reviews.headline: Not worth it
reviews.comments: I love white on my eyes.  Always run out of white first so I bought this eyeshadow.  just don't.  It's not worth it.  The white cakes if you use more than one layer and the glitter part....forget about it.  Just makes the white wet again after taking forever to dry and ughhh smudges it.

reviews.headline: Into It/Over It
reviews.comments:
The Into It/Over It is absolutely beautiful , my goodness!
Dries quick and stays on all day! This is definitely a unique look.

reviews.headline: Somewhat deceiving.
reviews.comments: I finally decided to purchase this because I had been looking at it since it arrived at my local store. I love how it looked when swatched on my hand and went with the color lover/fighter.  However, that swatch does not translate to the eyelids. While the crayon part went on fine, no issues there, the glitter was very patchy and the flecks of the glitter were so big. It looked so uneven on my eyelid and no matter what I did, I couldn't get them to even out or get the glitter to move at all once it was there.  I will likely use the crayon part of this product, but I'm gonna skip on the glitter. Will not repurchase.

reviews.headline: I love this
reviews.comments: I have always loved jelly eyeshadow and this one is awesome and last all night. I wore it on nye and still had some left the next morning.

reviews.headline: Skip this
reviews.comments: I purchased this to wear in NYE.  I didn't like this product at all.  The glitter/iridescent shadow did not go on smooth nor did it last.  Didn't like the color, unless you were using for an 80s themed party.

reviews.headline: Gorgeous, but tricky!
reviews.comments: I bought Into It/Over It and the glitter is so pretty, but it's hard to apply evenly. I only use this with a matte liquid eyeshadow as the base because liquid glitters tend to lift up powder. Apply in thin layers so it can dry and sting less.

reviews.headline: Build up in layers!
reviews.comments: These are so beautiful. I'm so shocked because I haven't been drawn to a Morphe product in a long time. I only use these with other liquid eyeshadows because in my experience any liquid glitter lifts up powder eyeshadow. The key with liquid eyeshadow or glitter is to build up in very thin layers. It's time consuming, but the longevity of the product is worth it. I use the about face matte eyeshadows as the base and then build the glitter by dabbing with my finger.

reviews.headline: Morphe Mistakes
reviews.comments: I purchased gunmetal sliver the glitter flakes are too big. No matter how many layers (i did three) it still looks like  one. cream shadow is black and it's just ok. maybe I should have tried a different primer So I exchanged it for  BFF and In to It.

reviews.headline: Love the look!
reviews.comments: I saw these in the catalogue and gave them a try. They add some serious sparkle when I want to be extra sparkly. One thing that was a little annoying at first was the cream didn't seem to glide on but when warmed up a little went on smooth.

reviews.headline: Gorgeous Color, Glitter Irritated My Eyelids
reviews.comments: The sparkle is beautifulllllll. i got the shade Lover/Fighter. the pink sparkle is gorgeous. it was a BIT too chunky for the eye even tho i love a chunky glitter it was almost like some of the pieces were too big. the stick shadow side laid down nicely, no smudges or clingy. even pigment. pigmented, one swipe color. it was a nice nude tone pink brownish color, i thought it was pretty. but im not sure why alot of glitter liquid eye shadow irritates my eye lids. this one unfortunately did the same, it feels like a cooling sensation until it dries down then it feels like a slight burning and when i blink it feels irritated. ill have to return which makes me sad but the color was pretty!!

reviews.headline: The liquid shadow stick is too watered down
reviews.comments: The liquid shadow stick is so watery it barely allows the glitter to stick. Even with the pencil as a base the formula was just too watered down even when shaken. There are definitely better glitter shadows out there

reviews.headline: Finally, a good quality affordable DM dupe!
reviews.comments: This is the first Danessa Myricks Infinite Chrome Flakes dupe I've tried that I'd actually spend money on. They're not AS brilliant as DM's, but at nearly half the price these are beautiful multichrome products. I also love that they come with a cream shadow built in in a complementary color to the chrome flakes.

reviews.headline: Holy glitter bomb
reviews.comments: I purchased Lover/Fighter. From the pictures where it shows it applied to the models' eyes, I was expecting a light glitter/shimmer effect from the liquid. However, it is super chunky flaky glitter madness. I think I would wear it for a halloween costume or if I'm going to a crazy party or something, but I will never wear this casually. I'm very glad I tried it on a day that I don't plan on leaving the house. The stick part was okay but I have better stick eyeshadows so I probably won't use that as much either. I might end up giving this to my 9-year-old niece for dress-up.

reviews.headline: Dang Morphe!!!
reviews.comments: Wow this product is really special. Shade BFF is the coolest duo chrome formula ive tried. Such a gorgeous and almost neon bright color with no fallout. Im in love. Im gonna buy every color

faceoff_positive.comments:
Morphe's Mixed Signals Dual-Ended Cream and Liquid Shadow Stick in "Love/Fighter" truly stands out as a remarkable addition to any makeup enthusiast's arsenal. This innovative product masterfully marries two essential formulas: a sumptuous cream shadow and a dazzling liquid shadow, both housed conveniently within a single stick.

The cream shadow, located at one end, boasts a remarkably smooth application that glides effortlessly across the eyelids. Its rich pigmentation allows for a variety of effects; whether you prefer a subtle wash of color for a more natural look or a bolder statement for a night out, this cream provides the flexibility to achieve your desired finish. The lightweight texture ensures comfort throughout the day, making it suitable for extended wear without feeling heavy or cakey.

Conversely, the liquid shadow at the opposite end is where the magic truly happens. This formulation delivers an eye-catching shimmer that instantly elevates any makeup look. It glides on smoothly, dries down quickly, and adheres beautifully to the skin, ensuring long-lasting wear without the fear of creasing. The shimmering effect strikes a perfect balanceradiant enough to draw attention but not overly dramatic, making it versatile for both day and night occasions.

One of the most impressive aspects of this dual-ended shadow stick is its versatility. Whether you're aiming for a laid-back daytime vibe or a striking evening ensemble, the "Love/Fighter" shades can be effortlessly blended and built up to create a myriad of stunning eye looks. Additionally, the compact design is perfect for travel, allowing for easy touch-ups throughout the day.

In summary, Morphe has truly excelled with the Mixed Signals Dual-Ended Shadow Stick. Combining quality, vibrant pigmentation, and user-friendly application, this product is a must-have for anyone looking to enhance their makeup routine with creativity and ease. If you're in search of a versatile tool that promises to inspire your artistic side, the "Love/Fighter" shadow stick is undoubtedly worth adding to your collection!
faceoff_positive.headline: Such a beautiful shadow stick

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review. I like multitasking makeup so I was excited to try this out. One side is amber colored chunky glitter than can be applied with the applicator for more opaque coverage or can put a less amount and blend using an eyeshadow brush if you don't mind a chunky glitter look on your eyelids. The other side is an eyeshadow stick that can be applied as an all over eyeshadow and blended with a brush, which I did. I also used a brush to swipe at the stick for a more precise eyeliner look. You can even use it as an eyebrow tint. I like the glitter and dark brown stock color together. You can make a few looks with this and I like that it has multiple uses. The glitter has some fallout and creasing so an eyeshadow primer is a good idea for all day hold. The eyeshadow stick matte dark brown showed on the folds of my eyelid creases when I don't apply eye primer but I have oily eyelids. The names are cute too. Overall, it's a nice multitasking product.
faceoff_negative.headline: Good 2 in 1 product
